        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer414676676" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer275160379246177061">HowOhHowOhHowOhHow did I make it this long without reading this book? It would feel weird to say I love it, it&apos;s that close... I always felt like chicana mestizas were talking about me, the greek-gringo mestiza... it all sounds right... but WHAT GENRE IS IT? It doesn&apos;t read like your typical essay or memoir. LOTS OF EXPOSITION (which I adore, but which usually gets nailed in workshop). So what is this book? Why do we care? Because we are writing a comps essay, first of all and second of all, bec</span>
  <span id="freeText275160379246177061" style="display:none">HowOhHowOhHowOhHow did I make it this long without reading this book? It would feel weird to say I love it, it's that close... I always felt like chicana mestizas were talking about me, the greek-gringo mestiza... it all sounds right... but WHAT GENRE IS IT? It doesn't read like your typical essay or memoir. LOTS OF EXPOSITION (which I adore, but which usually gets nailed in workshop). So what is this book? Why do we care? Because we are writing a comps essay, first of all and second of all, because when I write stuff like this people ask me what I was "trying" to do. So let me know. What is Anzaldua "trying to do"?</span>
