<div id="review_3133501905" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3133501905" />
    <a title="Nikhil" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11619849-nikhil"><img alt="Nikhil" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1344276050p2/11619849.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3133501905?book_show_action=true">Jan 03, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nikhil" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nikhil" href="/user/show/11619849-nikhil">Nikhil</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781879960855" href="/book/show/13427917-borderlands-la-frontera">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11619849-nikhil?shelf=poco">poco</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11619849-nikhil?shelf=theory">theory</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11619849-nikhil?shelf=american">american</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11619849-nikhil?shelf=chicana-chicano">chicana-chicano</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3133501905" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7761282398829200328">A text suggesting that the way for us to evolve/revolt out of hierarchies defined in binary opposition is to turn to those who live in the liminal spaces between these opposing forces - those who transgress/traverse/inhabit the boundary. Because these individuals internalize the contradictIons of the false dichotomy, they hold within themselves the seeds for a new consciousness free of the dichotomy. Anzaldua uses Chicana identity and her own development of a Chicana consciousness as a way of sh</span>
  <span id="freeText7761282398829200328" style="display:none">A text suggesting that the way for us to evolve/revolt out of hierarchies defined in binary opposition is to turn to those who live in the liminal spaces between these opposing forces - those who transgress/traverse/inhabit the boundary. Because these individuals internalize the contradictIons of the false dichotomy, they hold within themselves the seeds for a new consciousness free of the dichotomy. Anzaldua uses Chicana identity and her own development of a Chicana consciousness as a way of showing how to develop this new consciousness. In doing so she writes a new history for the Chicana/o peoples rooted in Aztec mother goddesses and the reclamation and reconstitution of a dismembered feminine divine destroyed both by indigenous patriarchy and settler colonialism. <br /><br />The structure of the text mirrors the hybrid identity it aims to create. The way to start creating this consciousness is to identify where competing narratives overlay and create friction within you, focus on that dissonance, and see what falls out. <br /><br />Overall, I did not find this as powerful as A Bridge Called My Back. Mainly, I did not have a strong emotive connection with the essays (I did with the poetry). I think this reflects that I do not find instinctual much of the religious symbology she uses around Aztec divinities; I suspect a similar argument using, e.g., Kali/Shiva in opposition to Hindutva would likely be much more powerful for me. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7761282398829200328" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

